<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>Mountaineers Head West to Take on No. 22 Arizona State</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/26/baseball-mountaineers-head-west-to-take-on-no-22-arizona-state</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/26/baseball-mountaineers-head-west-to-take-on-no-22-arizona-state</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="MatchupAtASU" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/26/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_ArizonaSt.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 17 West Virginia University baseball team travels out west to Tempe to take on the No. 22 Arizona State Sun Devils in a three-game weekend set at Phoenix Municipal Stadium. First pitch for Friday and Saturday is set for 9:30 p.m. with Sunday being at 8:00 p.m.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/26/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_ArizonaSt.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/26/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_ArizonaSt.jpg"><media:title>MatchupAtASU</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/26/BB26_Matchup_1920x1080_ArizonaSt.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 17:45:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58932</s:story_id></item><item><title>Four Mountaineers Earn CRCA All-American Honors</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/26/rifle-four-mountaineers-earn-crca-all-american-honors</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/26/rifle-four-mountaineers-earn-crca-all-american-honors</guid><category>Rifle</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Jennifer Kocher" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/26/DSC08365.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Four members of the West Virginia University rifle team took home a combined eight All-America honors from the Collegiate Rifle Coaches Association (CRCA), as announced by the organization.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/26/DSC08365.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/26/DSC08365.jpg"><media:title>Jennifer Kocher</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/26/DSC08365.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 15:33:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>8</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58931</s:story_id></item><item><title>Hellmann to Compete at NCAA Swimming and Diving Championships</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/26/mens-swimming-diving-hellmann-to-compete-at-ncaa-swimming-and-diving-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/26/mens-swimming-diving-hellmann-to-compete-at-ncaa-swimming-and-diving-championships</guid><category>Men's Swimming &amp; Diving</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Levi Hellmann vs. George Washington (Dec. 19, 2025)" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2025/12/20/_YNX7401.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Sophomore Levi Hellmann of the West Virginia University men's diving team is set to compete in two events at the 2026 NCAA Men's Swimming and Diving Championships on March 27-28, at McAuley Aquatic Center in Atlanta.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2025/12/20/_YNX7401.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/12/20/_YNX7401.jpg"><media:title>Levi Hellmann vs. George Washington (Dec. 19, 2025)</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/12/20/_YNX7401.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 12:43:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>7</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58930</s:story_id></item><item><title>Rowing’s 25th Year Begins with Split Squad Races</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/26/rowings-25th-year-begins-with-split-squad-races</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/26/rowings-25th-year-begins-with-split-squad-races</guid><category>Rowing</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Sarasota-RMU-Preview" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/26/ROW26_RaceDay_1920x1080.png" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University rowing team will open its 25th year this weekend as a split squad. WVU will race four boats at the Sarasota 2K in Sarasota, Florida, on Friday and Saturday, March 27-28, and two boats against Marietta and Robert Morris in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, on Saturday.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/26/ROW26_RaceDay_1920x1080.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/26/ROW26_RaceDay_1920x1080.png"><media:title>Sarasota-RMU-Preview</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/26/ROW26_RaceDay_1920x1080.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 11:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>12</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58929</s:story_id></item><item><title>Wetherholt Set to Make MLB Debut</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/25/baseball-wetherholt-set-to-make-mlb-debut</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/25/baseball-wetherholt-set-to-make-mlb-debut</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="JJ Wetherholt" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2024/4/26/DSC01001.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Former West Virginia University baseball player JJ Wetherholt is set to make his major league debut on Thursday, March 26, as the St. Louis Cardinals host the Tampa Bay Rays at 4:15 p.m. ET as part of MLB's Opening Day.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2024/4/26/DSC01001.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2024/4/26/DSC01001.jpg"><media:title>JJ Wetherholt</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2024/4/26/DSC01001.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 25 Mar 2026 15:40:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58928</s:story_id></item><item><ti